node.text: There's no need to wait until brunch to have a Bloody Mary because F&W Culinary Director at Large @justinchapple puts his Mad Genius spin on this fun, flavorful recipe. Tap the link in our bio for the recipe!

node.text: "The days of wilted lettuce are over," says Mad Genius and F&W Culinary Director At-large @justinchapple of his recipe. This salad gets texture from tender Little Gem lettuces, smoky broccolini, hearty kale and sliced almonds and is coated with a thick and creamy anchovy-laced dressing for maximum flavor potential. Tap the link in our bio for the recipe!

node.title: Charred Broccolini Caesar With Kale and Chickpeas

node.text: There's no need to wait until brunch to have a Bloody Mary because F&W Culinary Director at Large @justinchapple puts his Mad Genius spin on this fun, flavorful recipe. These chicken cutlets in a light, Parm-infused batter, and simmered in a lemony, chickeny cream sauce are an Italian-American red-sauce restaurant classic, paired perfectly with a crisp arugula salad or sauteed green beans. Tap the link in our bio for the recipe! 
🍗: @jazzy_the_princess 📸: @jencausey

node.text: In this episode of Chefs At Home, @meherwanirani of @chaipani and @spicewalla makes Spicy Green Banana Cutlets (Kaera Na Cutless), a traditional Parsi dish. Toasted spices, mashed green bananas, and panko come together to create these crispy, crunchy croquettes. Tap the link in our bio to watch the full episode on YouTube and get the recipe!
